		<p class="- topic/p " xtrf="/Users/Ruth/forks/docs-ng/dita/src/ag3/Misc/admin-datafiles.dita" xtrc="p:2;36:6">This path can be changed for each node at setup either via the Web UI setup wizard, using
			the REST API or using the Couchbase CLI.</p>
		<note type="note" class="- topic/note " xtrf="/Users/Ruth/forks/docs-ng/dita/src/ag3/Misc/admin-datafiles.dita" xtrc="note:1;38:21">Changing the data path for a node that is already part of a cluster permanently
			deletes the data stored.</note>
		<example class="- topic/example " xtrf="/Users/Ruth/forks/docs-ng/dita/src/ag3/Misc/admin-datafiles.dita" xtrc="example:1;40:12"><title class="- topic/title " xtrf="/Users/Ruth/forks/docs-ng/dita/src/ag3/Misc/admin-datafiles.dita" xtrc="title:2;40:19">Linux example:</title>
		<codeblock xml:space="preserve" class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock " xtrf="/Users/Ruth/forks/docs-ng/dita/src/ag3/Misc/admin-datafiles.dita" xtrc="codeblock:1;41:14">
couchbase-cli node-init -c node_IP:8091 \
	--node-init-data-path=new_path \
	-u user -p password
		</codeblock>
		</example>
		
		
		<example class="- topic/example " xtrf="/Users/Ruth/forks/docs-ng/dita/src/ag3/Misc/admin-datafiles.dita" xtrc="example:2;49:12"><title class="- topic/title " xtrf="/Users/Ruth/forks/docs-ng/dita/src/ag3/Misc/admin-datafiles.dita" xtrc="title:3;49:19">Windows example:</title>
		<codeblock xml:space="preserve" class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock " xtrf="/Users/Ruth/forks/docs-ng/dita/src/ag3/Misc/admin-datafiles.dita" xtrc="codeblock:2;50:14">
&gt; couchbase-cli node-init -c \
    node_IP:8091 --node-init-data-path=new_path \
    -u user -p password
</codeblock>
	</example>
		<p class="- topic/p " xtrf="/Users/Ruth/forks/docs-ng/dita/src/ag3/Misc/admin-datafiles.dita" xtrc="p:3;56:6">When using the command line tool, the data file and index file path settings cannot be changed
			individually. To change the setting individually, use the REST API. </p>
		<p class="- topic/p " xtrf="/Users/Ruth/forks/docs-ng/dita/src/ag3/Misc/admin-datafiles.dita" xtrc="p:4;58:6">Once a node or cluster has already been setup and is storing data, the path cannot be changed
			while the node is part of a running cluster. To change the path:</p>
		<ol class="- topic/ol " xtrf="/Users/Ruth/forks/docs-ng/dita/src/ag3/Misc/admin-datafiles.dita" xtrc="ol:1;60:7">
			<li class="- topic/li " xtrf="/Users/Ruth/forks/docs-ng/dita/src/ag3/Misc/admin-datafiles.dita" xtrc="li:1;61:8">Remove the node from the cluster.</li>
			<li class="- topic/li " xtrf="/Users/Ruth/forks/docs-ng/dita/src/ag3/Misc/admin-datafiles.dita" xtrc="li:2;62:8">Change the path on a running node either via the REST API or using the Couchbase
					CLI (commands above). This change does not actually take effect until the node
					is restarted. </li>
			<li class="- topic/li " xtrf="/Users/Ruth/forks/docs-ng/dita/src/ag3/Misc/admin-datafiles.dita" xtrc="li:3;65:8">Shut the node down.</li>
			<li class="- topic/li " xtrf="/Users/Ruth/forks/docs-ng/dita/src/ag3/Misc/admin-datafiles.dita" xtrc="li:4;66:8">Copy all the data files from their original location into the new
				location.</li>
		</ol>
	</body>
